{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Jk5m6JMvmkLimPki2ST3sH","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, rusqlite 0.31 is used. Let me check if it has `query_row_cached` method.\n\nActually, in rusqlite 0.31+, there's a `CachedStatement` mechanism and `Connection::prepare_cached`. For `query_row`, the connection might have a `query_row_cached` method.\n\nLet me look at what's happening: `load_projection_cursor` calls `connection.query_row(...)` which internally calls `prepare` on the connection. If we pass a `Transaction` to it (via `Deref`), it should work the same.\n \nSo `load_projection_cursor` takes `&Connection`, and when called from `read_search_in_tx` with `&tx`, the transaction dereferences to the connection. That's one prepare call via `query_row`. The other three prepares per search are likely coming from `fts_match` doing its own prepare, plus potentially `vec0_match` and `canonical_lookup` when vector queries are involved.\n\nBut if `RoutedEmbedder` isn't returning a vector in the fixture, I'd only expect 2 prepares total, not 4. Let me check what the actual test fixture is doing and whether the embedder is actually producing vectors there.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2436,"cache_read_input_tokens":35863,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2436},"output_tokens":26,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"38adc285-4437-4bbf-a855-0849e65f1132","uuid":"db502ee6-9411-4f96-8496-6b68d0caae8b"}
