{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_013HFP6XT5sP2ACaifQ9z7XA","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, now I have everything I need. Let me implement the changes:\n\n1. Add `use rusqlite::StatementStatus;` to the imports (or use the full path)\n2. Add `search_prepare_misses: AtomicU64` to Engine struct\n3. Initialize it in `open`\n4. Add accessor methods to Engine\n5. Change `read_search_in_tx` signature and implementation\n6. Update the call in `search_inner`\n7. Write the test file\n\nLet me write the code. Let me first write the test file (RED state), then make the code changes.\n\n\nActually, I should first add the counter + accessor WITHOUT switching to `prepare_cached`. Then write the test, run it (RED), then switch to `prepare_cached`, then run again (GREEN). So I'll add the `search_prepare_misses` field to Engine and have `read_search_in_tx` increment it on every prepare call, write the test to verify the counter works, then refactor to use `prepare_cached` and watch the counter drop.\n\nFor the implementation, I need to handle the counter increments before each `tx.prepare()` call—for vec0_match and canonical_lookup that's straightforward, but `soft_fallback_probe` uses `tx.query_row()` which internally calls prepare, so I'll need to account for that too.\n\nActually, since `soft_fallback_probe` doesn't even run in the test fixture, I'll focus on instrumenting just the three paths that actually execute: vec0_match, canonical_lookup, and fts_match, each with a counter increment before their `tx.prepare()` call.\n\nFor the RED phase, the baseline count will be 300 (3 × 100 iterations), and the assertion `assert!(count <= 32)` will fail as expected. In GREEN, I'll switch those three to `prepare_cached` and add the same counter logic, which should drop the count to 3 total (one per statement), easily passing the assertion.\n\nNow I'm ready to implement the actual code changes. I need to modify the Engine struct definition, initialization, the search_inner function, and read_search_in_tx to add the counter and switch to prepare_cached in GREEN. I'll also add a test accessor method to expose the counter value.\n\nModifying lib.rs...","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1295,"cache_read_input_tokens":76518,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1295},"output_tokens":35,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"38adc285-4437-4bbf-a855-0849e65f1132","uuid":"b6576014-1fb2-431a-bf12-b618c85dae3b"}
