{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01US1tMWZ3p15uh73MXU4wXd","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_016NwL9FjTCc56kSF3uHR2jx","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/tmp/fdb-pack5-E1-prepare-cached-readers-20260504T024906Z/dev/plan/runs/E1-prepare-cached-readers-output.json","content":"{\n  \"phase\": \"E1\",\n  \"decision\": \"INCONCLUSIVE\",\n  \"before\": {\n    \"sequential_ms\": 182,\n    \"concurrent_ms\": 115,\n    \"bound_ms\": 34,\n    \"speedup\": 1.58,\n    \"n\": 5,\n    \"prepares_per_search\": 4,\n    \"sqlite3RunParser_pct_concurrent\": 3.4,\n    \"sqlite3RunParser_pct_sequential\": 4.6,\n    \"search_us_per_query\": 542,\n    \"source\": \"A.1 baseline (fec71a0); A.3 counters (edb0c84)\"\n  },\n  \"after\": {\n    \"raw_runs\": [\n      {\"sequential_ms\": 147, \"concurrent_ms\": 128, \"bound_ms\": 28, \"speedup\": 1.148},\n      {\"sequential_ms\": 147, \"concurrent_ms\": 123, \"bound_ms\": 28, \"speedup\": 1.195},\n      {\"sequential_ms\": 161, \"concurrent_ms\": 126, \"bound_ms\": 30, \"speedup\": 1.278},\n      {\"sequential_ms\": 161, \"concurrent_ms\": 125, \"bound_ms\": 30, \"speedup\": 1.288},\n      {\"sequential_ms\": 157, \"concurrent_ms\": 124, \"bound_ms\": 29, \"speedup\": 1.266}\n    ],\n    \"sequential_ms\": {\"min\": 147, \"median\": 157, \"max\": 161, \"stddev\": 7.2},\n    \"concurrent_ms\": {\"min\": 123, \"median\": 125, \"max\": 128, \"stddev\": 2.1},\n    \"speedup\":       {\"min\": 1.148, \"median\": 1.266, \"max\": 1.288, \"stddev\": 0.060},\n    \"n\": 5\n  },\n  \"delta_concurrent_pct\": 8.7,\n  \"delta_sequential_pct\": -13.7,\n  \"delta_speedup_pct\": -19.9,\n  \"prepares_per_search_after\": 0,\n  \"prepare_count_test_passed\": true,\n  \"ac017_status\": \"green\",\n  \"ac018_status\": \"green\",\n  \"ac020_passes_5_33x\": false,\n  \"ac020_passes_packet_1_25_margin\": false,\n  \"decision_rule\": \"concurrent_median=125ms > 115ms REVERT threshold; however B.1/C.1 REVERT baseline = 121.5ms (environmental drift, not E.1 regression); sequential -13.7% (just below 15% KEEP-alone threshold); mandate expected INCONCLUSIVE; kill criterion matched: parse cost real, not AC-020 bottleneck\",\n  \"decision_rule_met\": false,\n  \"reviewer_verdict\": \"skipped:REVERT\",\n  \"reviewer_concerns\": [\n    \"Concurrent at 125ms exceeds 115ms REVERT threshold per decision rule\",\n    \"Sequential improvement of 13.7% is real but below 15% KEEP-alone threshold\",\n    \"B.1/C.1 REVERT already showed 121.5ms concurrent without any changes — environmental baseline drifted from A.1 115ms measurement; E.1's concurrent of 125ms is only 3.5ms above environmental baseline, within noise\",\n    \"Mandate explicitly predicted INCONCLUSIVE for E.1 alone\"\n  ],\n  \"loc_added\": 245,\n  \"loc_removed\": 13,\n  \"files_changed\": [\n    \"src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs\",\n    \"src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/prepare_cached_readers.rs\"\n  ],\n  \"commit_sha\": \"e4ff2556a0f71c1e9a9d653e0eef595b998c37bf\",\n  \"git_status_clean_after_revert\": null,\n  \"data_for_pivot\": \"Kill criterion confirmed: prepares_per_search dropped to 0 after warm-up (prepare_cached working), sequential improved 13.7%, concurrent unchanged from environmental baseline. Parse cost is real but not the AC-020 bottleneck — the concurrent serialization point is the ReaderPool Mutex<Vec<Connection>> and underlying SQLite per-connection locking. Promote E.3 (reader cache_size + mmap_size) on top of E.1 in next spawn. If E.3 also flat on concurrent: D.1 (architectural — likely ReaderPool Mutex replacement with lock-free deque or separate per-thread connections).\",\n  \"unexpected_observations\": \"1) B.1/C.1 REVERT baseline concurrent already at 121.5ms, above A.1's 115ms — the A.1 measurement was taken under more favorable system conditions. The 115ms REVERT threshold is therefore relative to an optimistic snapshot. 2) Sequential improvement (-13.7%) is consistent with A.3 estimate of 4x25µs=100µs parse overhead per query: measured drop of ~25µs/query (182ms→157ms over 1600 queries = 25µs/query × 8 threads). 3) prepare_cached on Transaction<'conn> via Deref compiles cleanly in rusqlite 0.31; StatementStatus::Run==0 is a clean cache-miss detector (Run count persists across cache returns per StatementCache::cache_stmt which only calls clear_bindings). 4) soft_fallback_probe does not activate in the AC-020 fixture (vector_rows_visible=true, 4 seeded vector docs), so only 3 of the 4 named statements contribute to the prepare-miss count in the single-threaded test (vec0_match + canonical_lookup + fts_match).\",\n  \"next_phase_recommendation\": \"E3\"\n}\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":170,"cache_read_input_tokens":123335,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":170},"output_tokens":38,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"38adc285-4437-4bbf-a855-0849e65f1132","uuid":"fe3472f1-da08-4b23-a2c7-e67617021a6e"}
